**[High] "Edit Metadata" is a guaranteed no-op — verified in the running app.**

`editMetadata` pushes `/system-security-plans/${uuid}`, but the Overview is the **index child of that exact route** (`system-security-plan-editor` → `''` → `system-security-plan-overview` in `src/router/index.ts`). Clicking the button navigates to the page the user is already on: verified via Playwright — URL unchanged, no modal, nothing happens.

The handler is pre-existing, but on `main` this button sat in the Actions section next to an explicit *"some editing functionality is still in development"* notice. This PR deletes that notice and promotes the button into the card header as a primary affordance — presenting dead functionality as live, which is worse than before.

Suggested fix: wire it to a real metadata editor — a Dialog with title/version fields PUTting to the SSP metadata (the POA&M section has a `MetadataEditForm` pattern to follow in `src/components/poam/MetadataEditForm.vue`). If that's out of scope for this round, disable the button with a tooltip explaining why, like the System Characteristics Edit button — don't leave it silently dead.
