Comment (src/views/system-security-plans/SystemSecurityPlanCharacteristicsView.vue:167):
**[High] There is now no way to edit System Characteristics anywhere — yet a working editor exists in the codebase.**

This Edit button is hard-`disabled`, and this PR also (a) deleted `SystemSecurityPlanCharacteristicsEditorView.vue` and (b) removed the Overview's "Edit System Characteristics" action. Verified in the running app: every path to editing characteristics is gone.

The git notes justify this with *"instead of inventing a new metadata/characteristics update endpoint that is not present in this UI"* — but that premise is factually wrong. `src/components/SystemCharacteristicsForm.vue` (still in the tree, now orphaned with zero consumers after this PR deleted its only importer) calls `useSystemSecurityPlanStore().updateCharacteristics()`, which PUTs to `/api/oscal/system-security-plans/{id}/system-characteristics` — form and endpoint both exist and were wired together on the deleted view.

Suggested fix: enable this button and open `SystemCharacteristicsForm` in a Dialog (consistent with how every other section in this refactor edits in modals), refreshing `characteristics` on its `updated` event. That is strictly less work than what was deleted.
