Comment (src/views/system-security-plans/SystemSecurityPlanControlImplementationView.vue:166):
**[Medium] "Create Component" under every statement is permanently dead — a disabled button wired to a stub.**

Verified in the running app: after creating a statement, the natural next step is attaching a component implementation, and every one of these buttons is hard-`disabled`. Even if enabled, `createComponent()` is a stub: `alert('Create Component functionality is in development')`.

This is pre-existing, but a refactor whose stated purpose is making SSP control-implementation editing usable shouldn't restyle a permanently dead button and ship it — there is currently **no way to add a by-component to a statement** in the entire flow, which strands the statement-editing workflow this PR otherwise polished (the new `StatementByComponent` partial supports edit/delete but nothing can create one).

Suggested fix, in order of preference: (1) implement it — a create form posting to `.../statements/{uuid}/by-components` would mirror `handleSaveStatementByComponent`'s PUT one line below and can reuse `ByComponentEditForm`'s field set; (2) if that's a follow-up, remove the button (or replace with a tooltip-explained disabled state) so users aren't presented a dead control at the exact moment they need it.
